    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 5,
      "text": "FROM : D. M. Ladd",
      "status": "pending_image_audit"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 6,
      "text": "SUBJECT: FLYING SAUCERS",
      "status": "pending_image_audit"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 7,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 8,
      "text": "I took a call from [unclear] of your office Saturday relative to a letter Mr. Winchell received from a man in Los Angeles. He stated that the Bureau had no objection to a column on this letter if the Bureau was not mentioned.",
      "status": "needs_image_check"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 9,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 10,
      "text": "I told him that whatever he did with reference to writing the story concerning this letter was entirely up to him and wouldn't in any way affect the Bureau one way or another inasmuch as the handling of flying saucers with the Air Corps was a matter of primary interest to them. He stated, \"To hell with the Air Force.\" He just didn't want to release the information if it would affect the Bureau.",
      "status": "pending_image_audit"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 11,
      "status": "blank"
    },
